adverbs.description: immemorially (comparative more immemorially, superlative most immemorially)

entries.meaning: In an immemorial manner, from time immemorial.
examples: Yet, O reader, the brave woman accepted the lot, and took up the cry which had been its sign immemorially, and which thenceforward was to be her salutation without change—“Unclean, unclean!”
